Resolve driver topology cleanly. If you wish to override a module output manually, you must sever the module output structurally to an unmapped wire, and apply explicit priority routing (MUX) onto the final physical port.
```verilog
module safe_sub_top(input valid, input override, output [3:0] flag);
  wire [3:0] internal_flag;

  // Secure instance drives onto an exclusive isolated internal wire
  child_core u_core (.v_in(valid), .flag_out(internal_flag));

  // A single, discrete assignment utilizes a logical multiplexer to govern the port
  assign flag = override ? 4'hF : internal_flag;
endmodule
```

