During complex SoC block assembly, auto-routing tools frequently accidentally connect disparate validation flags to the identical top-level dummy port. SystemVerilog explicitly restricts this by using the `logic` data type, which physically cannot legally sustain multiple mathematical assignments, throwing a compilation error cleanly rather than the synthesis tool doing so 30 minutes later.

